# manifest.json rules

## Required shape

```json
{
  "name": "Tool name (user-facing, plain English)",
  "id": "kebab-case-unique-id",
  "api": "1.0.0",
  "main": "src/code.js",
  "ui": "src/ui.html",
  "editorType": ["figma"],
  "networkAccess": {
    "allowedDomains": ["*"],
    "reasoning": "Public open HTTP APIs only; no API keys in generated tools."
  },
  "documentAccess": "dynamic-page"
}
```

## Field rules

- **`name`** is user-facing. Use natural English. No "Plugin" suffix. Example: `"Bento Grid"`, not `"Bento Grid Plugin"`.
- **`id`** is internal. Kebab-case, unique. Example: `"bento-grid-tool"`.
- **`main`** points to the compiled JS, which lives next to `code.ts`. `npx tsc` produces `src/code.js` from `src/code.ts`.
- **`networkAccess`** is pre-set to `["*"]` for public open APIs (no API keys). **Do not change** per generation run. See `docs/10-network-open-apis.md`. If this file changes in git, the human re-imports the dev plugin once in Figma.
- **`documentAccess: "dynamic-page"`** allows the plugin to access pages other than the current one. Keep this default. Sandbox code must use `figma.getNodeByIdAsync`, not `figma.getNodeById`, when resolving ids from `toolState` (see `docs/07-plugin-practices.md`).

## Do not add

- No `parameters` block — V1 tools don't use prompted parameters.
- No `commands` array unless the tool genuinely has multiple distinct actions (e.g., "Cleanup duplicates" + "Cleanup unused styles" in one plugin). Single-purpose tools omit `commands`.
- No `relaunchButtons` — handle re-opening via the standard plugin run flow.
